This paper deals with the problem of detecting browser fingerprinting scripts using machine learning techniques. The paper discusses the use of heuristic approaches, supervised machine learning, and then proposes a semi-supervised approach. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely categories. The paper also discusses the methodology used for detecting fingerprinting scripts, which makes cs.SE (Software Engineering) a likely category. Finally, the paper discusses the analysis of the detected scripts, which makes cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) a possible category.
